%yoann: introduce Ref and QLock and why need them (and maybe reference Libcore book)
%claude:
Because multiple threads and procs access [[Window]]s concurrently---the
mouse thread, the keyboard thread, the window's own [[winctl]] thread,
and filesystem worker threads---[[Window]] embeds a [[Ref]] for
reference counting and a [[QLock]] for mutual exclusion.
The [[Ref]] prevents a window from being freed while another thread
still holds a pointer to it---for instance, the mouse thread may be
partway through a resize or delete operation on a window while a
filesystem worker thread is simultaneously servicing a read on
that same window's [[/mnt/wsys/cons]].  Without reference counting,
the window could be deallocated under the worker's feet.
The [[QLock]] serializes access to fields that can be modified from
different threads (see \book{Libcore} for the details of these
synchronization primitives).

