\section{Channels creation}

% threads communicate and synchronized between each other through
% messages on channels
%alt: locks or mutex or semaphores or monitor
%claude:
[[rio]]'s threads communicate exclusively through channels rather than
shared variables protected by locks.
The [[exitchan]] is the simplest example: [[threadmain()]] blocks
on a [[recv()]] on this channel, and the mouse thread sends a
message when the user selects ``Exit''.
Many more channels will be created later---each new window gets its own
set of channels for keyboard, mouse, and control messages.

<<global [[exitchan]]>>=
// chan<unit> (listener = threadmain, sender = mousethread(Exit) | ?)
