\subsection{Worker allocator: [[xfidinit()]]}

%yoann: explain need for worker allocator and maybe ASCII diagram comm with master
%claude:
Rather than creating a new thread for every 9P request,
[[rio]] pools worker threads via two channels: [[cxfidalloc]]
to request a worker, and [[cxfidfree]] to return one.
The allocator thread manages the pool, creating new workers
only when needed:
%
\begin{verbatim}
  filsysproc (master)          xfidallocthread (allocator)
       |                              |
       |--- recv(cxfidalloc) -------->|  "give me a worker"
       |<-- Xfid* -------------------|
       |                              |
       |    ... dispatch 9P work ...  |
       |                              |
       |--- send(cxfidfree, x) ----->|  "worker done, take it back"
       |                              |
\end{verbatim}

