%claude:
The mouse thread is more complex than the keyboard thread because
mouse events have a dual nature: some belong to the application (e.g.,
left-click for text selection) and some belong to the window manager
(e.g., right-click for the system menu, border clicks for move/resize).
The thread must decide for each event whether to {dispatch} it to the
window thread ([[sending = true]]) or handle it locally as a windowing
system operation.

