\subsection{Windowing system mouse events}

%claude:
When a mouse event is not forwarded to the application, the mouse thread
handles it as a windowing system operation. It first determines which
window is under the cursor with [<wpointto()>], then dispatches based on
the button pressed: left-click on an unfocused window brings it to the
front, middle-click opens the edit menu (cut/paste),
and right-click opens the system menu (New/Resize/Move/Delete/Hide/Exit).
Clicking on a window's border initiates a move or resize operation.

