%yoann: explain Drain issue
%claude:
After a move or resize operation completes, there may be leftover
mouse events (button-held messages) still queued from the I/O proc.
If the thread returned to the main [[alt()]] loop immediately,
those stale events would be misinterpreted as new actions. So
[[Drain]] spins through [[readmouse()]] until all buttons are
released, discarding the residual events, then jumps back to
[[Again]] to re-evaluate the mouse position with a clean state.

