[<winctl()>] is the heart of each window. It is the thread where
keyboard input gets processed, mouse events get interpreted, and
control messages (resize, delete, hide) take effect. Every window
gets its own instance, making each window an autonomous concurrent
entity with its own event loop---the ``active object'' pattern.

