%claude:
The functions sent through the channel are the 9P operation
handlers: [<xfidattach()>], [<xfidopen()>], [<xfidread()>],
[<xfidwrite()>], [<xfidclose()>], and [<xfidflush()>]. Each one
implements one step of the file protocol---for instance, when
a client reads [[/mnt/wsys/cons]], the master sends [<xfidread()>]
to a worker, which then retrieves console data from the
appropriate window. These handlers are covered in later chapters.



