Before diving into the heart of window management, I will cover
the simpler topic of cursor handling.
[[rio]] uses different cursor shapes to provide visual feedback about
what operation is possible: a plus sign for creating windows, a box for
moving, a gunsight for deleting, and directional arrows when hovering
over window borders and corners.

