\section{[[Wctlmesg]]}

%claude:
The [[Wctlmesg]] structure is the message type sent from the mouse thread
(or other sources) to a window's [[winctl]] thread through its [[cctl]]
channel.
The message carries the operation type (Reshaped, Moved, etc.),
a rectangle (for operations that change geometry), and an optional
image (the new window layer after a resize or move).
Note the past tense in the enum names (Reshaped, not Reshape)---the
image has already been allocated by the time the message arrives; the
window thread just needs to adopt it.

