%claude:
Window creation is the most important operation in [[rio]]---it ties
together all the subsystems: graphics (allocating a layer on the
desktop), concurrency (creating a new [[winctl]] thread), the filesystem
(mounting [[/mnt/wsys]] for the new window), and processes (forking
a shell).
When the user selects ``New'' from the system menu, [<sweep()>] lets
them draw a rectangle, then [<new()>] creates everything needed for the
new window (see Section~\ref{sec:trace-new-window} for the high-level
overview).

