\subsection{Namespace adjustments: [[filsysmount()]]}

%claude:
This is the key step that makes [[rio]]'s virtualization work.
[[filsysmount()]] mounts [[rio]]'s client pipe onto [[/mnt/wsys]],
passing the window ID as the mount spec so that [[rio]] knows which
window the client belongs to. Then it binds [[/mnt/wsys]] before
[[/dev]], so that [[/dev/cons]], [[/dev/mouse]], etc.\ resolve to
[[rio]]'s virtual files rather than the real device files.
After that, the child process simply opens [[/dev/cons]] for
stdin and stdout---but these are now served by [[rio]].

