signal) to the entire process group. Then it kicks off
[[deletetimeoutproc]] as a safety net and calls [<wclosewin()>] to remove
the window from the screen immediately. The window's thread does not
exit yet---it waits for the [[Exited]] message that comes later when
all filesystem references are closed.

