%claude:
Unhiding reverses the trick: [<wunhide()>] allocates a real layer (via
[[allocwindow]]) and sends a [[Reshaped]] message. The [[Reshaped]]
handler swaps the off-screen image for the new on-screen layer,
publishes it via [<wsetname()>], and the window reappears.
The menu integration is handled by the [[default]] case in the
[[button3menu]] switch---any menu index past the standard entries
corresponds to a hidden window.

<<[[button3menu()]] cases>>=
