\subsection{Reading a directory}

% important case! Qdir! (Qwsysdir will be explained later)

%claude:
To read a directory, the server iterates over [[dirtab]] and calls
[[dostat()]] on each entry, which serializes a [[Dir]] structure into
the 9P wire format via [[convD2M]]. The [[o]] and [[e]] variables
implement offset-based pagination: the server formats all entries but
only copies those whose cumulative offset falls within the requested
range. This is needed because 9P directory reads must be deterministic
and restartable from any byte offset.

<<[[filsysread()]] other locals>>=
Dirtab *d;
@
<<[[filsysread()]] cases>>=
case Qdir:
case Qwsysdir:
    d = dirtab;
    d++;	/* first entry is '.' */
    for(i=0; d->name != nil && i<e; i+=len){
        len = dostat(fs, WIN(x->f->qid), d, b+n, x->req.count - n, clock);
        if(len <= BIT16SZ)
            break;
        if(i >= o)
            n += len;
        d++;
    }
    break;
@
