\subsubsection{Tab}

%claude:
Tab stops are configurable via the [[tabstop]] environment variable
(defaulting to 4 if not set). The value is stored in pixels as
[[frm.maxtab]] = [[tabstop]] $\times$ the width of a ``0'' character.
This means tab alignment adapts automatically to the font---a
proportional font with narrow characters gets narrower tab stops.
%claude:
Tab alignment is computed at drawing time by [<_frnewwid0>]: it rounds
up the current x position to the next multiple of [[maxtab]] (relative
to the left margin), ensuring a minimum width of one space ([[minwid]])
so that tabs always produce visible whitespace.

<<[[Frame]] text fields>>=
ushort	maxtab;		/* max size of tab, in pixels */
@

<<[[frinit()]] initialize other fields>>=
f->maxtab = 8 * stringwidth(ft, "0");
@



