\subsection{Other clicks}

%claude:
When the mouse is not inside the scrollbar, [[wmousectl]] dispatches
based on which button was pressed. Left-click (button 1) triggers
text selection via [<wselect>]; middle and right clicks were already
intercepted by [<mousethread>] for the menu and window management,
so they do not normally reach here.
%claude:
Mouse buttons 4 and 5 (the scroll wheel) are translated into
synthetic [[Kscrolloneup]] and [[Kscrollonedown]] key events by
calling [<wkeyctl>]---an elegant reuse that makes the scroll wheel
behave identically to the keyboard scroll keys, without any
special-case code in the scrolling logic.

<<[[winctl()]] WMouse case if not mouseopen>>=
